HEADWORD: Unplat
<hw>Un*plat"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>plat</ets>.]</ety> <def>To take out the folds or
twists of, as something previously platted; to unfold; to
unwreathe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unplausive</ent>⟦br⟧
